    <stitle>CAB: 4100, 4200, 4300 AND 4400 MODELS - REMOVE - WINDSHIELD WASHER BOTTLE AND/OR PUMP MOTOR</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
        <title>WINDSHIELD WASHER BOTTLE AND/OR PUMP MOTOR</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove Windshield Washer Bottle and/or Pump Motor on Standard Cab, Extended Cab and Crew Cab for all
                Models
            </title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f16026120">Figure 120</hotlnk>
                for all models before July 2001 or
                <hotlnk xrefid="f16026121">Figure 121</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="f16026121"/>
                for all models after July 2001 or
                <hotlnk xrefid="f16026122">Figure 122</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="f16026122"/>
                for all models after June 2002 for Items in parentheses.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Unlatch hood on both sides and tilt hood to fully open position.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If the pump motor is removable and is being replaced, it is necessary to remove the washer
                        bottle before removing the pump motor.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two hex flanged bolts (Item 1) securing washer bottle (Item 2) with pump motor
                    (Item 3) to washer bottle bracket (Item 4). Save hex flanged bolts for installation. Remove washer
                    bottle from washer bottle bracket and lay it forward to access the pump motor.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Since two different types of washer bottles and pump motors (Items 2 and 3) may be found
                    on vehicles, always check Parts Catalog before removing pump motor (Item 3) from washer bottle (Item
                    2).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect wiring harness connector (Item 5) from pump motor (Item 3).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use a suitable container to catch washer fluid and empty all the washer fluid from
                    washer bottle (Item 2). Remove washer hose (Item 6) from pump motor outlet fitting (Item 7).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If pump motor (Item 3) is being replaced, carefully pull pump motor from washer bottle
                    (Item 2).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If washer bottle (Item 2) is being replaced, disconnect wiring harness connector (Item
                    8) from washer bottle wiring harness connector (Item 9) coming from low fluid sensor (Item 10) in
                    washer bottle.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove washer bottle (Item 2) from vehicle.</para>
            </step1>
